{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "icon": "COP2/vector", "internal": "snap_point_ql", "version": "2", "namespace": "qLib"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Snap/Point qL"], "extent": [46, 64]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["interface version 2"]}], "extent": [64, 88]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Sets up a snapping point (and/or direction) based on an input geometry."], "extent": [88, 167]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Snaptools provides a toolkit to ", {"type": "q", "text": ["snap"]}, " or align one geometry to another,\nusing up to three points on the source and target geometry for matching."], "extent": [167, 314]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["A snapping network consists of one or more Snap/Point nodes, then a Snap/Xform qL node.\nEach Point can add a new snapping point (or direction), and the Xform performs\nthe transformation, based on the information set up by the Point nodes."], "extent": [314, 554]}, {"level": 1, "id": "workflow", "container": true, "type": "workflow_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["Workflow"], "role": "section", "extent": [554, 573], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib--snap_point_ql-2/snaptools_main.png", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [573, 609]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["Procedural snapping: after defining source (red) and target (green) reference points,\n  the torus is snapped and aligned onto the target surface (a grid)."]}], "extent": [609, 770]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"type": "strong", "text": ["How to set up a point (snapping component)"]}], "extent": [770, 816]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Open a Parameter panel for a Snap Point qL SOP\n  (also, make sure the OP has the display flag)"], "extent": [816, 914]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Specify the reference geometry\n  (it\u2019s either the connected input, or another SOP\n  drag-and-dropped into the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["SOP Path"]}, " field)"], "extent": [914, 1045]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Press the ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Display Selection Geometry"]}, ": this displays the reference geometry"], "extent": [1045, 1125]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Specify the geometry components"], "extent": [1125, 1160]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["for point: use src/tgt coord A/B/C"], "extent": [1160, 1197]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["for dir: use src/tgt Aim or Up, from/to an already existing A/B/C point"], "extent": [1197, 1271]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["press ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Done Editing"]}], "extent": [1271, 1295]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["use the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Add New\u2026"]}, " convenience buttons to build next element of the OP chain"], "extent": [1295, 1381]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1381, 1393], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["SOP Path"], "extent": [1393, 1407], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["If enabled, this path specifies the geometry where the snapping component\n        (point or direction) will be extracted from (", {"type": "em", "text": ["reference geometry"]}, ").\n        If disabled, the input geometry is used."], "extent": [1407, 1615]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Display Selection Geo"], "extent": [1615, 1642], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Pressing this button will display the reference geometry.\n        If there are selected primitives and/or points (see below),\n        only those parts will be displayed."], "extent": [1642, 1821]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 8, "role": "item", "extent": [1821, 1834], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Workflow tip: press this button before tuning the parameters.\n            It ensures proper visualization of the geometry component selections."], "extent": [1834, 1991]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Selection Mode"], "extent": [1991, 2011], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The way of extracting a 3d point coordinate from the reference geometry."], "extent": [2011, 2093]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["Point(s)"], "extent": [2093, 2111], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The resulting 3d point will be the average of the selected geometry points.\n            The ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Select Primitive(s)"]}, " and ", {"type": "em", "text": ["Select Point(s)"]}, " fields can be used to\n            select the primitives and points (by their indices)."], "extent": [2111, 2347]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["Point on Curve"], "extent": [2347, 2371], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The 3d position will be of a single point from a curve primitive."], "extent": [2371, 2450]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 8, "text": ["Constant"], "extent": [2450, 2468], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The point coordinates can be typed directly."], "extent": [2468, 2526]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["\u2026"], "extent": [2526, 2535], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["\u2026"], "extent": [2535, 2548]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Done Editing"], "extent": [2548, 2566], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Press this button once all parameters are set up."], "extent": [2566, 2625]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 8, "role": "item", "extent": [2625, 2638], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["Workflow tip: ", {"type": "em", "text": ["always"]}, " press this button once all parameters are set\n            up as desired. This ensures that the proper geometry and data is passed to\n            downstream operators."], "extent": [2638, 2842]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2842, 2851], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::snap_xform_ql::2", "type": "link", "text": ["Snap/Xform qL SOP"], "exists": true}], "extent": [2851, 2909]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/qLib::snap_point_ql::2", "type": "link", "text": ["Snap/Point qL SOP"], "exists": true}], "extent": [2909, 2969]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}, {"level": 1, "id": "todo", "container": true, "type": "todo_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["To Do"], "role": "section", "extent": [2969, 2981], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["Option for extracting directions from (per-point) vector attributes"], "extent": [2981, 3057]}], "container": true}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "relnotes", "container": true, "type": "relnotes_section", "indent": 0, "text": ["Release Notes"], "role": "section", "extent": [3057, 3081], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["interface version 2"]}, " \u2014"], "extent": [3081, 3113]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["2014-02-26"], "extent": [3113, 3129], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["First prototype, with reworked UI"], "extent": [3129, 3175]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"type": "em", "text": ["interface version 1"]}, " \u2014"], "extent": [3175, 3206]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["2013-05-14"], "extent": [3206, 3222], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["First prototype."], "extent": [3222, 3249]}], "container": true}], "container": true}]}], "title": ["Snap/Point qL"], "summary": ["Sets up a snapping point (and/or direction) based on an input geometry."]}